6:
Are we finished yet? I'm starting to
grow bored.
9:
Relax, the scan's finally done. Your
physical make-up is quite
extraordinary—though not in a good
way, I'm afraid.
11:
Keep utilizing your powers, and you'll
find yourself bedridden before long.
14:
I-it's that bad?! We should've gotten
you checked out sooner...
18:
I refuse to leave all the work to Rem,
Miss Emilia, and especially Barusu.
22:
Er... I get where you're coming from,
but..
26:
Anyway, can you fix me? Or can you
not?
29:
Based on the scan results, I have a
potential solution. You could use
elemental gems as a source of
power, much like this tool does.
31:
However, for the amount of energy
you require, the conversion machine
will have to run on only the purest
gems.
34:
...In other words, you need us to get
you some rare gems.
37:
You catch on quickly. Honestly, I'd
prefer to simply charge money for
the prototypes I'm going to lend
you...
38:
But I suppose I can make a few extra
and let you walk away with them.
42:
Hold it. Are you trying to leave me
behind?
45:
You should have called for me.
Come on, let's go.
49:
Whoa, hey, wait! You're not
supposed to be pushing yourself,
remember?
51:
Besides, we're the ones with plenty
of experience in the Kaleidoscope.
You should wait back—
54:
Your search will go faster with the
aid of my power. Or do you intend to
track down gems with your nose?
62:
It will be fine. I even told Rem I'm
coming and have her permission to
do so.
66:
All right, in that case... You'll leave
the fighting to us, yeah?
69:
Of course. I intend to slack off as
much as possible.
79:
Punch that wall there as hard as you
can.
84:
Who the hell designed this place?!
No way a normal person would've
found this path...
89:
See, bringing me was the correct
decision. Now move.
97:
No way... How often do you come
across a natural deposit this big?
103:
The professor should be able to
make plenty of prototypes with all
this.
106:
Do your best to carry everything
back.
112: Yeah, yeah, we got it, Your Highness.
116:
Here, try this prototype bracelet on.
If it fits, attach a gem to it.
119: I just felt a rush of mana...
121:
It was a brief reaction, but that
proves it works! Now if you attach a
gem of higher quality...
124:
Good thing we've got plenty! Use as
much as you need!
128:
The experiment was a grand
success! Well, what do you think?
131: It worked? Sister, how do you feel?
134:
I'm not fully healed... But I think it's
easier to move around now.
139:
Hey, that's good, right? Sounds like
you'll be able to stay decently
healthy.
142:
It's better than nothing at the very
least. This might work out better
than I expected.
148:
I'm relieved that we actually found
something that can help you, Sister...
152:
I'm sorry I worried you, Rem. I won't
be falling over anymore.
155:
Ahem... I don't mean to break up the
party, but what are you going to do
about your gem supply going
forward?
157: Huh? Don't tell me this isn't enough...
161:
I would say, out of everything here,
you have about five gems that are
useable.
168:
Most of what you brought is lacking
in quality. Only the purest of gems
will suffice as a power supply for the
young lady here.
171:
They sell gems in Palpebra, don't
they?
173:
For hefty prices, yes. You could
probably afford a mansion for the
amount of money you'll need to
shell out.
176:
You said you'd help me if I'm ever in
trouble, remember?
179:
You should keep your promises,
especially to Sister.
184:
Okay, no need to gang up on me!
Full disclaimer: we're pretty broke—
190:
Do you hear that, Rem? He'll find
high-paying jobs for us.
197:
Yes, Sister. Not only that, but he'll
also help us do those jobs.
201:
Right... I'll look out for you guys until
the day you find a way home.
206:
I'm glad to hear that you'll honor
your promise.
208:
I'll help you out on your adventures,
so I expect the same level of
cooperation from you.
